            , In July, 1824, I owed Shearman 1l. 16s. 6d., which I paid to a man - I cannot say whether the prisoner is the man: here is the receipt the person gave me.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM SHEARMAN. When I took the prisoner he said, voluntarily, that he had spent Tucker's money, and I ought to have had it.</p>
